ct damage now?</span><hr size=1> I only play my wizard to level 63, without VT key, tier 3 zone access, so this only represent my concerns.<br>
<br>
As of now, everyone pretty agree wizard is master of damage. Certainly druid deal less damage than wizard in every single level. But what about mage?<br>
<br>
If you just compare raw numbers, it is indeed the fact. However, we must account for this: Relatively FREE focus item. (ok, they actually cost 20pp to buy a spell, or 500pp as a ep turn in. jewelry bag is a sp spell, which still worth no more than 20k)<br>
<br>
There exist 2 easy quest that will yield a SH2 and MP2 item, but none of the focus 3/4 item is cheap. Althought the focus item that mage summon does not have good stat, it is still a focus item. Remember the price of ODS before and now? The price raise 5 folds after it become MP3, so the value of focus is high.<br>
<br>
Now, as I said focus 2 is easily available, so wizard can clearly outdamage mage with superior spell, but what about higher level?<br>
<br>
You don't have to read this if you are in elemental plane with VT/whatever else focus. You are the best, have no problem at all. Sadly not everyone is as uber as you.<br>
<br>
Note: mage earring save 15% mana (avg 7.5%) bracer 20% more damage (average 10%) ring 15% spell haste<br>
<br>
LV 49<br>
<br>
Wiz<br>
Ice Comet 1110 dmg 400 mana 6.3 cast time<br>
Moified damage/mana (innate crit) 2.844<br>
DPS 180.59<br>
<br>
Mage<br>
Lava Bolt 810 300 7<br>
Modified damage/mana with focus 3.21 <br>
DPS 149.75<br>
<br>
So ice comet is less efficient but more damage/mana. If you use Rend then it will be inferior in both area.<br>
<br>
LV 57<br>
<br>
Wiz<br>
Draught of Ice 716 215 3<br>
damage/mana 3.41 DPS 244.63<br>
<br>
Mage<br>
Shock of Steel 795 275 6<br>
damage/mana 3.43 DPS 171.47<br>
<br>
Again Mage still have better damage/mana ratio. Consider wizard can only do damage from mana, shouldn't wizard nuke be more efficient as well?<br>
<br>
LV 60<br>
Wiz <br>
Sun Strike 1615 450 7<br>
damage/mana 3.68 DPS 236.48<br>
<br>
Mage<br>
Shock of Fiery Blade 1005 334 6.8<br>
damage/mana 3.58 DPS 191.26<br>
<br>
Seeking Flame of Seukor 1024 320 7<br>
damage/mana 3.81 DPS 189.31<br>
<br>
For the first time after 59 levels, wizard truely out nuke mage -- if mage does not use the bolt.<br>
<br>
Sadly, just one level later, Firebolt of Tallon destroy the tiny wizard's advantage.<br>
<br>
LV 61<br>
Wiz<br>
Sun Strike 1615 450 7<br>
damage/mana 3.68 DPS 236.48<br>
<br>
Garrison's Superior Sundering 2100 540 8<br>
damage/mana 3.99 DPS 269.06<br>
<br>
Mag<br>
Firebolt of Tallon 1920 500 7<br>
damage/mana 4.57 DPS 354.96<br>
<br>
So, a vendor bought spell and 3x500pp EP spell completely destroy the ultra rare best of the best damage.<br>
<br>
In fact, even with Agnarr's Thunder, wizard still lags behind mage in both mana efficient and DPS. The situation won't change even with Strike of Solusek.<br>
<br>
And those are about DIRECT DAMAGE only, Mage also have a pet with 40-70DPS (their board said so). Mage can also buff other caster/pet in group by providing focus item/pet only item. Mage charm isn't useful everywhere and does have risk so let's not consider that.<br>
<br>
So mage can provide better DPS, better DPM, better &quot;buff&quot;, which would you choose to group with?<br>
<br>
Te above number is not calculated with any focus item for wizard. Why? How much is a ID4, SH4, MP4 would cost you? How much the same thing cost it to mage? How many wizard have those focus (or equivalent)? FoT is already a 300pp vendor spell, why it should outdamage SS/GSS/AT/SoS which all cost at least 50 times more? Is wizard master of direct damage or should repharse to &quot;master of direct damage if and only if you are uber&quot;<br>
<br>
Some people may argue wizard have better AA for DD. But dont forget, when a wizard invest 18 point into SCFM, a mage can invest into SCM 3 and MC 2, which also helps his damage. So maybe after 300 AA, wizard is better....<br>
<br>
Now, people will say mage do not specialize in evoc. That is not my problem. Anyone is freely to choose their specialization, and I do know mage spec in evo. My druid spec in evo too unlike many other doing alter.<br>
<br>
People also say wizard can quad kite, so I am complaining too much. However able to quad kite still does not change the fact master of damage is outnuke by another class and that shoul be fixed. Speaking of solo, mage can also solo and at 65, their charm can provide much better exp even with the high risk.<br>
<br>
People also say bolt is harder to land which justify their godly damage/mana and DPS. However, is that difficulty justify mage to nuke above wizard, which wizard suppose to be master of direct damage? Just like charm, the difficulty of landing a bolt is greatly exagerate.<br>
<br>
And guess what? From mobhunter SOE is fixing LoS issue, which may make bolt easier to land. At the same time SoE decide range damage is too powerful, so expect mroe aggro for archery and DD. Mage still have a pet to contribute damage, while wizard must be more careful to DD now, even the DD is weaker.<br>
<br>
Solution:<br>
1) Make GSS more frequently drop and make EER a vendor spell. EER is an inferior spell compare to FoT. The 1 level difference is joke (60 to 61 is fast).<br>
<br>
2) Wizard's DD should always be a lot better than mage DD, and that should not require the wiz to have God level item. Both class is almost pure damage and mage have a pet, so wizard DD MUST be better or it will be a mage without pet. To accomplish this:<br>
<br>
a) Nerf mage, which is the worst solution so don't do it.<br>
b) More easier obtain, wizard only focus item. By easier it better to be same difficulty as getting and handing in EP which what current mage enjoy.<br>
c) Reduce mana, cast time/increase damage for all wizard spell from lv 1 to 65.<br>
d) Make wizard spell even less resistable. Not just only on draught.<br>
e) more ice flame style spell which works for more spell.<br>
<br>
Once again, numbers clearly show mage outnuke wizard unless wizard have godly equipment. Wizard should be master of direct damage, not master of translocate. You may feel wizard is very powerful even with normal gear, but mage still DD much better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=milaru00>Milaru 00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1576<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/6/03 9:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is wizard the master of direct damage now?</span><hr size=1> god, this is the worse post yet :/<br>
