 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=carighanmaconar01>CarighanMaconar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/8/03 10:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is wizard the master of direct damage now?</span><hr size=1> Direct comparison of Mage vs. Wizard nuke is (sorry) just plain <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">stupid</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->. It's like saying Mages are better at Crowd Control than Enchanters because their Mezz can be focused to 1,6 secs cast time, while Enchanter's 2,5 secs cannot be focused...<br>
<br>
While Mage nukes may often be of better ratio, see the fact that a Wizard, apart from saving a small number of mana at the lower end of his mana bar for evacs, does cast <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>nothing</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> except nukes. He also, with familiars, has a higher mana regen than mages, but leave this out of this thing for now. So a Wizard can contribute <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">all</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> his mana regen (not mana, see evac) to damage. A Mage can not. He needs to keep Burnout on his pet, and with it's short duration, the spell quickly gets costly. He often utilizes Damage Shields and Mod Rods for other party member.<br>
<br>
So while a Wizard <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">does</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> have less mana efficiency than Mages in his Nukes, Mages also don't nearly have as much percentage of their mana regen to contribute to Nukes. The balance <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">is</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> delicate, but it is there, IMHO! <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55795">Carighan Maconar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Enchantress of the 60th Circle<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Member of the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.nebelwelt.de/eq/index.htm">Namenlose Bruderschaft</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on Solusek Ro<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.mutedfaith.com/quiz/qz4.htm&quot;" target="&quot;new&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mutedfaith.com/images/time.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.mutedfaith.com/quiz/qz4.htm&quot;" target="&quot;new&quot;">find your element</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.mutedfaith.com&quot;" target="&quot;new&quot;">mutedfaith.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jear@graffeswizardcompilation>Jear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/9/03 5:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> LOL and so it continues</span><hr size=1> Well I love my wizard. I would never think a mage would be able to do the same Direct damage then a wizard. (of same lvl ofcouse and close to same AAs) We have as I have tried to point out on several ocations what is called a arsenal of nukes. Mages don't have cold nukes. and mages also mostly (well atleast those I know) use Conjuration as their shpere of specialisation, but they have 2 spheres where their nukes are Evoc and Conju.<br>
