<br>
That's like saying &quot;so, other than going faster, how is a drag racer faster than my car?&quot;  You just answered it, the quote I gave was &quot;Just FYI, Mages do MORE DD than Wizards level 34-38.&quot; which is absolutely true.  Is our spell more mana efficient?  Yes.  Does the specialization Evocation which Mages tend not to choose make a (very slight at this level) difference?  Sure.  Does the Wizard spell cast faster?  Yep, for every 6 blasts from them we can cast 7.<br>
<br>
But bottom line, their DD spell is more damaging than ours.  And while this is only true this level range, all the other factors you list are true EVERY OTHER level range.  This is an aberration that is the result of poor design by Verant - design they refused to fix, and SOE will do no different.<br>
<br>
The point was, he said &quot;Well I love my wizard. I would never think a mage would be able to do the same Direct damage then a wizard.&quot; So I was pointing out where this was not only true, it was true that they had a blast that did MORE.  Now, some mages try to pretend their Damage Sheild damage mysteriously doesn't come from them, but it adds to their damage.  So does their Pet, by a very large amount.  This damage is virtually mana-free.  That's where the concern comes up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xymryk>Xymryk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/12/03 12:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LOL and so it continues</span><hr size=1> Don't forget the cinder bolt you are referring to also requires LoS.  Which is not that big of a limitation, but does slightly diminish its usefulness. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=katrel>Katrel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/18/03 3:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LOL and so it continues</span><hr size=1> I 2box both 65 mage and wizard, both have about 60 aa's. There is no comparison on DD. The wizard wins hands down. SoS is an obscene spell, crits over 6k. If my mage uses bolt his over his 65 DD, his DPS goes up and mana efficiency goes way down. LoS hits alot, but can still be frustrating in large raids or while doing trials when DSP matters alot and having your bolt get intercepted by a bench.<br>
